Allocate a user‐mode buffer of at least 0x100 bytes, zero it out, and then call DeviceIoControl with that same buffer as both the input and output buffer. After the call the first 8 bytes will be the 64-bit key. Example in C:

```
BYTE buf[0x100] = {0};
DWORD bytesReturned;
BOOL ok = DeviceIoControl(
    hDevice,                    // handle to the driver
    0x9C40240B,                 // IOCTL
    buf, 0x100,                 // lpInBuffer, nInBufferSize
    buf, 0x100,                 // lpOutBuffer, nOutBufferSize
    &bytesReturned,
    NULL
);
if (ok) {
    UINT64 key = *(UINT64*)buf;
    // key now holds the 64-bit XOR key
}
```

